An Act relative to the creation of an endometriosis task force.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 6A of the General Laws shall be amended by adding after section 16GG the
2 following new section:-
3 Section 16HH. (a) Notwithstanding any general or special law to the contrary, the
4 executive office of health and human services shall establish an endometriosis task force. The
5 task force shall consist of: the secretary of the executive office of health and human services or a
6 designee, who shall serve as chair; the commissioner of the department of public health or a
7 designee; the commissioner of the division of insurance or a designee; the director of Medicaid
8 or a designee; 2 individuals appointed by the NAACP New England Area Conference with
9 experience in healthcare in Massachusetts, and 9 persons to be appointed by the secretary of the
10 executive office of health and human services, 2 of whom shall be representatives from the
11 Massachusetts Medical Society Alliance, Inc. appointed in consultation with their relevant
12 specialty chapters, 1 of whom shall be a representative of the New England Medical Association,
13 1 of whom shall be a representative of the Tufts Center for Black Maternal Health and
14 Reproductive Justice, 1 of whom shall be a representative from the Massachusetts Association of
1 of 2

15 Health Plans, Inc., 1 of whom shall be a representative from commercial health insurance plans
16 or managed care organizations doing business in the commonwealth, 1 of whom shall be an
17 individual with a diagnosis of endometriosis, 1 of whom shall be a representative of a
18 pharmaceutical company that manufactures a drug or device for detecting, preventing or treating
19 endometriosis and 1 of whom shall be a representative of a research, advocacy or support
20 organization primarily serving individuals with a diagnosis of endometriosis.
21 (b) The task force shall: (i) develop and annually update a summary of the advances
22 made in research on and treatment and diagnosis of endometriosis; (ii) develop and annually
23 update a summary of the advances made in access to care for individuals with a diagnosis of
24 endometriosis; (iii) monitor endometriosis research, services and support activities across the
25 commonwealth, including coordination of the commonwealth's activities and programs with
26 respect to endometriosis; (iv) develop and annually update a comprehensive strategic plan to
27 improve health outcomes for individuals with a diagnosis of endometriosis, including
28 recommendations to: (1) advance research on endometriosis; (2) improve public awareness and
29 recognition of endometriosis; (3) improve health care delivery for individuals with a diagnosis of
30 endometriosis; (4) improve the early and accurate diagnosis of endometriosis; and (5)
31 systematically advance the full spectrum of biomedical research on endometriosis; and (v)
32 develop and annually update the progress made in implementing such comprehensive strategic
33 plan.
34 (c) The task force shall submit its recommendations to the governor, the clerks of the
35 house of representatives and senate, and the joint committee on public health annually not later
36 than December 31 of each year.
